## Scenario

Describe the problem and context clearly.

Include:

- What needs to be built or changed
- Why it is needed
- Where the context lives (sources, systems, etc.)

If external knowledge is required, mention it explicitly.

---

## Acceptance Tests

Define verifiable outcomes. Prefer bullet points or Gherkin style.

- The system MUST ...
- The system SHOULD ...
- The system MAY ...

Keep them atomic and testable.

---

## Sources

External references (URLs only).

- https://...
- https://...

---

## Context Queries

Executable MCP queries to enrich the context.

Use the format:

- mcp obsidian: <query>

Examples:

- mcp obsidian: architecture of MCP in Obsidian
- mcp obsidian: best practices for designing skills
- mcp obsidian: troubleshooting MCP query execution

---

## Notes (optional)

Any additional constraints, assumptions or clarifications.

- Edge cases
- Dependencies
- Known limitations
